# SimplexaLabs Landing Page — Cursor Rules

## Architecture (Feature-Sliced)

- **`src/components/ui/`** — Low-level, reusable atomic components (Button, Card, CtaBorderWrap, ShimmerText). No business logic.
- **`src/components/layout/`** — Layout pieces (Header, Footer).
- **`src/features/[feature-name]/`** — Encapsulated flows: components, hooks, services, constants, types (e.g. `features/chat`).
- **`src/hooks/`** — Global shared hooks (e.g. useIntersectionObserver).
- **`src/services/`** — External API clients and wrappers (e.g. `services/api/chatClient.ts`).
- **`src/lib/`** — Utilities: `cn()`, `logger`. No business logic.
- **`src/types/`** — Centralized TypeScript interfaces. Prefer importing from `@/types` for shared types.
- **`src/sections/`** — Page sections (composition only). Section-specific constants can live in the section file or a co-located `constants.ts`.

When adding new code, place it in the correct slice. New features → `features/[name]`. New shared UI → `components/ui` or `components/`.

## TypeScript

- Use **strict typing**. Avoid `any` at all costs.
- Prefer **discriminated unions** for state (e.g. `{ status: 'idle' } | { status: 'loading' } | { status: 'error'; message: string }`).
- Put shared interfaces in `src/types/` and re-export from `types/index.ts`.

## Components & class names

- Use **`cn()`** from `@/lib/utils` for dynamic class names (Tailwind-safe merging).
- Prefer **composition** and small, focused components. Avoid prop drilling; use Context only when necessary.

## Constants & config

- Move **large config objects** out of TSX into `constants/` or feature-level `constants.ts`.
- Keep section/feature constants close to where they’re used when they’re not shared.

## Error handling

- Use **`logger`** from `@/lib/logger` for errors (e.g. `logger.error(message, context)`). Do not use raw `console.error` in app code.
- The app is wrapped in **ErrorBoundary**; critical UI can use error boundaries for granular fallbacks.

## Naming

- Use **declarative names**: e.g. `isPanelOpen`, `hasNewMessage` instead of `open`, `hasNew`.
- Prefer **clear, readable names** over brevity.

## Accessibility & semantics

- Use **semantic HTML** (main, section, article, aside) and **ARIA** where needed (aria-label, aria-live, aria-expanded).
- Ensure interactive elements (chat, accordions, CTAs) have appropriate labels and roles.

## Marketing (existing rule)

- Act as a professional marketer for this landing: prioritize conversion, clarity, and positioning. Suggest better copy or structure when relevant.
